# StableBoundaryLayerGSPT AI Guidance

## Language and Runtime
- Language: Julia
- Use project environment: julia --project=.
- Primary SCM entrypoint: scm/run_case.jl

## SCM State and Grid Contract
- State vector layout is block-structured:
  [Ts, U[1], ..., U[N], V[1], ..., V[N], theta[1], ..., theta[N]]
- Core diffusion stencil is nearest-neighbor in 1D vertical space:
  node i couples only to i-1, i, i+1
- Uniform-grid default uses scalar dz in SCM operators

## Solvers and Jacobian Path
- Stiff solver: OrdinaryDiffEq.Rodas5P
- Jacobian mode flag: --solver-jacobian {autodiff|finite}
- Sparsity flag: --jacobian-sparsity {dense|banded}
- Banded mode uses a sparse Jacobian prototype consistent with the local 1D stencil

## AD and Type-Stability Rules
- Keep RHS helper logic type-generic (Float64 and Dual-compatible)
- Do not force Float64 casts in closure helpers used during Jacobian construction
- Workspace/scratch buffers must safely adapt when Dual numbers are present

## SHEBA Operational Defaults
- SHEBA initial theta-lapse-rate default: 0.004 K/m
- Runtime override: --theta-lapse-rate <K/m>
- Typical high-top experiment setup: N=250, dz=2.0 (about 500 m top)
- SHEBA safety floor: ts_min = 220 K
- Non-local h bounds are clamp-controlled (defaults commonly 20 m to 400 m unless overridden)

## Non-local Height Clamp Contract
- Apply runtime clamp before closure coefficients:
  h_eff = max(nonlocal_h_min, min(h_diagnosed, nonlocal_h_max))

## Output Artifacts
- Main diagnostics: time_series.csv, summary.json, payload.jld2
- Primary figure for thermal structure: fig03_hovmoller_theta
